de.uka.ipd.sdq.beagle.core

Class ResourceDemandingInternalAction

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.uka.ipd.sdq.beagle.core.ResourceDemandingInternalAction
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    MeasurableSeffElement, java.io.Serializable

    public class ResourceDemandingInternalAction
extends java.lang.Object
implements MeasurableSeffElement
    Models an internal action demanding resources of a specific type when being executed.

    The internal action applies to a specific resource type. The resource type describes both the resource that is demanded and the unit the demandâ€™s value is expressed in. To support extensibility, these types are represented as strings with no inherent restrictions. However, the following Strings should be used per convention:

    • RESOURCE_TYPE_CPU
    • RESOURCE_TYPE_CPU_MS
    • RESOURCE_TYPE_HDD_READ
    • RESOURCE_TYPE_HDD_READ_MS
    • RESOURCE_TYPE_HDD_WRITE
    • RESOURCE_TYPE_HDD_WRITE_MS
    • RESOURCE_TYPE_HDD
    • RESOURCE_TYPE_HDD_MS
    • RESOURCE_TYPE_NETWORK
    • RESOURCE_TYPE_NETWORK_MS
    Resource types should use the suffix "_MS" exactly when they should be measured device dependent in the time unit ms.

    Serialized Form

    • Constructor Detail

      • ResourceDemandingInternalAction

        public ResourceDemandingInternalAction(java.lang.String resourceType,
                                       CodeSection action)
        Creates a ResourceDemandingInternalAction for a specific resource type using a given code section.
        Parameters:
        resourceType - The resource type of this internal action that should be measured. See class description for resource types, that should be used per convention. Must not be null. Must not be empty.
        action - A valid code section for this resource demanding internal action. The first line of the code section marks the beginning of this internal action (inclusive). The last line of the code section marks the end of this internal action (inclusive). Must not be null.
